quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  73,1,"O you enwrapped one,"
  73,2,"stand up{1}during the night except a little–",footnotes:1:[‘Stand up’ denotes adoration of Allah in night prayers.]
  73,3,"for half of it or reduce it a little"
  73,4,"or add to it, and chant the Recital{1}slowly and distinctly.",footnotes:1:[The Arabic word used is <i>Qur’an</i> which literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.]
  73,5,"Indeed, We are about to cast upon you<sup>sg </sup>a heavy word."
  73,6,"The vigil of the night is indeed more intense{1}and more upright for articulation.",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: Abu ‘Amr and Ibn ‘Amer read it as: “…is indeed more suitable and…”]
  73,7,"Indeed, in the daytime you<sup>sg </sup>have lengthy work to do."
  73,8,"So remember the Name of your<sup>sg </sup>Lord and devote yourself to Him with<i>(solemn) </i>devotion."
  73,9,"<i>(He is) </i>the Lord{1}of the East and the West; there is no god but He, so take Him as a Trustee.",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: All except for Nafie’, Ibn Kathir, Abu ‘Amr, Hafs and Abu Ja’far read it as: “…devotion— <sub><small>9</small></sub>9 the Lord of the East…”]
  73,10,"And endure patiently what they say, and withdraw from them politely."
